river mortis ™ 2024-03-27 5:47 AM
it's hard to tell without hearing you cause everyone's voice is different (so a good voice teacher is best, it's become more common to offer it virtually too since covid), but generally strengthening your head tone in your lower register will help stabilize. other general stuff is breath support, not holding tension anywhere in your body (but especially your jaw/throat) etc but beyond that it'd really depend on where you're at
